socket() It is used to create a socket object
.bind((HOST, PORT)) It is used to associate the socket with a specific network interface and port number
.listen() It enables a server to accept connections. It makes the server a “listening” socket
.accept() This method blocks execution and waits for an incoming connection.
.connect() This method is used to connect to the server
.connect_ex() 
.send()
.recv()
.close()


Transmission Control Protocol (TCP Sockets)

Why should you use TCP? The Transmission Control Protocol (TCP):

Is reliable: Packets dropped in the network are detected and retransmitted by the sender.

Has in-order data delivery: Data is read by your application in the order it was written by the sender.